ssociated Press] Vanguard News Nigeria.  Uganda police spokesperson, Elly Matte, on Thursday reported that four people were struck dead by lightning in the southwestern Ugandan district of Kanungu. September 12, 2019 In "News" Six people were killed and 11 others critically injured when lightning struck on Thursday in Uganda's northern district of Pader. Police Commander, Tom Bainomugisha, told Xinhua by telephone that the group of people was gathering under a big tree when the lightning struck during a morning drizzle. “The group had… November 8, 2019 In "Foreign" At least 13 Muslim worshippers were killed and 15 hurt when lightning struck a mosque in a remote village in northeast Bangladesh as they held special Ramadan prayers, police said on Saturday. August 11, 2012 In "News"